&lt;div class="book-toc-list"&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/preface.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;作者序 · 要成功，更要成长&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;卡耐基讲述本书写作缘起——15年实践与研究的结晶，以及那些改变人生的真实故事。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/part-1.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;第一篇 · 基本技巧&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;待人接物的三大基本技巧：不批评、真诚赞赏、激发需求。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch01.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;01 · 待人接物的第一大忌&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;批评、指责和抱怨无济于事，只会激起对方的防御和反击。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch02.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;02 · 这种说话方式非常值钱&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;真心实意地赞赏他人——这是激发潜能、赢得合作的最有效方式。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch03.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;03 · 让整个世界前来为你助力&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;唤起他人的渴望——站在对方的角度思考问题，才能影响他人。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/part-2.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;第二篇 · 如何让大家都喜欢你&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;六种让人喜欢你的方法：真诚关心、微笑、记住名字、倾听、谈论对方的兴趣、让对方感到重要。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch04.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;04 · 这样做，谁会不喜欢你？&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;真诚地关心他人——这是建立友谊的基础，也是影响力的起点。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch05.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;05 · 这能留下美好的第一印象&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;微笑——最简单却最有效的社交武器，无需成本却能创造价值。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch06.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;06 · 这会让人一下子喜欢上你&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;记住对方的名字——这在他们听来是世上最美、最重要的声音。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch07.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;07 · 怎样才叫&amp;#34;会聊天&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;做一个好听众，鼓励对方谈论他们自己——这是成为受欢迎的人的秘诀。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch08.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;08 · 提高你的影响力&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;谈论对方感兴趣的话题——这是抓住注意力、建立连接的最有效方式。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch09.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;09 · 一句话焐热人心&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;让对方感到自己重要——并且要真心实意地这样做，这是赢得人心的核心法则。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/part-3.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;第三篇 · 如何有逻辑地说服他人&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;十二种说服技巧：从避免争论到下达挑战书，让对方心甘情愿地接受你的观点。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch10.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;10 · 第一大忌：伤敌一万，自损八千&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;避免争论——你赢不了争论，即使辩赢了也失去了人心和合作的可能。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch11.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;11 · 第二大忌：一句惹怒全世界的话&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;尊重他人意见，永远不要说&amp;#34;你错了&amp;#34;——这是避免冲突的黄金法则。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch12.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;12 · 拆招卸力&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;如果错了，立即坦率地承认——这能化解敌意，让对手无话可说。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch13.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;13 · 开口前结局已定&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;以友善的方式开始——友好的态度是一切说服工作的前提和基础。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch14.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;14 · 如何引导对方的思路&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;让对方立刻说&amp;#34;是&amp;#34;——苏格拉底式提问，引导对方进入肯定的思维模式。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch15.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;15 · 贵人语迟&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;让对方多说话——倾听是最好的说服，让对方充分表达自己的观点。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch16.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;16 · 洗脑术：如何让人深信不疑&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;让对方觉得这是他的主意——人们更相信自己的结论，而非被告知的答案。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch17.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;17 · 如何让别人关注你&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;试着从对方的角度看问题——换位思考是理解他人、化解冲突的关键。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch18.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;18 · 提高你的人格魅力&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;同情对方的处境和想法——同理心是最有力的说服工具和人格魅力来源。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch19.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;19 · 如何让人乐意服你&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;诉诸更高尚的动机——人们愿意相信自己的行为出于高尚的理由。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch20.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;20 · 说不透时，卖个故事&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;把你的想法戏剧化——用生动的故事和行动打动对方，而非枯燥的说教。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch21.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;21 · 最后一招，下封战书&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;提出挑战——激发对方的竞争欲望和自我证明的驱动力。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/part-4.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;第四篇 · 成为一个领袖&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;九种领导技巧：如何改变他人而不冒犯人或引起反感、愤怒或怨恨。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch22.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;22 · 如何让大家都尊重你&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;从赞美和真诚的欣赏开始——在批评之前先肯定，这是领导力的第一法则。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch23.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;23 · 批评但不招人恨&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;间接地指出他人的错误——用暗示代替直接批评，保全对方的自尊。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch24.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;24 · 服人而不得罪人&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;先谈自己的错误，再批评对方——以身作则是最有说服力的批评方式。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch25.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;25 · 世界上没有任何人能指使我&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;用提问代替命令——没有人喜欢被支配，提问让人感到被尊重。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch26.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;26 · 第一大忌：犯众怒&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;给对方留足面子——即使你完全正确，也不要伤害对方的尊严。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch27.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;27 · 水涨船高：激励下属成事儿&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;赞扬每一次进步——真诚的赞赏比物质奖励更能激发人的潜能。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch28.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;28 · 你的期望永远不会落空&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;给人一个无法辜负的美名——设定高期望会让对方努力不辜负你的信任。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch29.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;29 · 让人乐意照你说的去改&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;让改正错误变得容易——鼓励而非打击，让对方看到改进的希望。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/ch30.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;30 · 让人乐意照你说的去做&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;让对方乐意做你建议的事——赋予意义和价值感，而非强迫执行。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
 &lt;a class="toc-row" href="https://uynajgi.github.io/yuulibrary/books/how-to-win-friends/q-and-a.html"&gt;
 &lt;span class="toc-row-title"&gt;答疑 · 这本书到底有多大作用&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-desc"&gt;常见疑问解答：如何最大化利用本书原则，如何看到实际效果。&lt;/span&gt;
 
 &lt;span class="toc-row-arrow"&gt;›&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
 
